Rona Alison Fairhead CBEIndependent Director, Pepsico, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships55$275,000
Background

		Ms. Rona Alison Fairhead, CBE, serves as the Non-Executive Chairman of HSBC North America Holdings Inc. Ms. Fairhead served as the Chief Executive Officer of FT Group at The Financial Times Limited. Ms. Fairhead served as the Chief Executive Officer of Financial Times Group Limited, a subsidiary of Pearson Plc from May 2006 to 2013. She served as Deputy Finance Director of Pearson PLC since October 2001. From 1996 to 2001, she served at Imperial Chemical Industries Plc ... (ICI Plc) as Director of Planning & Acquisitions from 1996 to 1997; Executive Vice President for Planning & Communications from 1997 to 1998 and as an Executive Vice President for Strategy & Group Control from 1998 to 2001. She previously served as Pearson's Chief Financial Officer from 2002 to 2006. She served as a Member of the ICI Executive Board from 1997 to 2001 and Chairman of the Investment Committee of the ICI pension fund. After acting as an Independent Consultant to British Aerospace PLC, from 1990 to 1991, she joined Short Brothers PLC in 1994 as Executive Vice President for Strategy & Communications. She became Executive Vice President and General Manager, Bombardier Aerospace Services (UK) in 1996. In her early career, she worked for Bain & Co and Morgan Stanley. She has been an Independent Director of Pepsico, Inc. since March 13, 2014. She served as the Chairman of the Board at BBC Trust since October 9, 2014 until January 18, 2017. She served as a Non-Executive Director of The Economist Group Limited since July 2005. She has almost 30 years of experience in finance and global business. She served as the Chairman of Interactive Data Holdings Corporation from September 21, 2007 to July 29, 2010 and Financial Times Group Ltd. until April 2013. She served as an Executive Director of Pearson PLC, Pension Arm and Pearson plc from June 1, 2002 to April 2013. She served as a Director of Financial Times Group Limited until April 2013. She is also a Trustee Director of the Pearson Group Pension Fund and has served as a Non Executive Director of Harvard Business School Publishing since 2002. She served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of HSBC Holdings PLC since March 1, 2004 until April 22, 2016. She served as Director of Interactive Data Holdings Corporation from February 20, 2007 to July 29, 2010. She was educated at Yarm Grammar School and holds a first class honors degree in Law from St. Catharine's College, Cambridge. She was named a Commander of the Order of the British Empire in 2012 and was appointed as a British Business Ambassador in 2014. She is a member of the United Kingdom Government's Cabinet Office, supporting the Prime Minister to ensure effective development, coordination and implantation of policy and operations across all government departments. She also gained an MBA from Harvard Business School, USA.Read Full Background




